27
00:02:09,540 --> 00:02:10,660
Nope, no mistake.

28
00:02:10,870 --> 00:02:11,870
She's my pick.

29
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,120
Get in touch

30
00:02:13,250 --> 00:02:14,660
with her agency

31
00:02:14,790 --> 00:02:16,080
and start working on the contract.

32
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:18,000
I want it signed

33
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,040
and on my desk by Monday. Got it?

34
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:21,040
Mr. Sheng,

35
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,160
don't you think

36
00:02:22,330 --> 00:02:24,370
she's a bit too new for this?

37
00:02:24,540 --> 00:02:25,750
Does she really fit the Sheng Group

38
00:02:25,830 --> 00:02:26,120
image?

39
00:02:26,290 --> 00:02:28,540
We're choosing a spokesperson,

40
00:02:28,660 --> 00:02:30,580
not just a pretty face.

41
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,750
We need someone with potential.

42
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:33,790
Understand?

43
00:02:38,540 --> 00:02:40,950
I told you that you'd lose the bet.

44
00:02:41,830 --> 00:02:43,040
Here we go.

45
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,910
You heard that, right?

46
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:48,290
You two teamed up against me!

47
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:49,830
It doesn't count, Lanshan.

48
00:02:51,540 --> 00:02:53,250
We're married,

49
00:02:53,540 --> 00:02:54,830
